<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Randgold Resources Q4 attrib loss narrows.</title>
<headline>Randgold Resources Q4 attrib loss narrows.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-01-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Quarter to end-Dec versus twelve months to September 30, 1996</p>
<p>			(million $ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Attributable loss			4.16  vs 5.31</p>
<p>    Revenue				    15.22 vs 2.08</p>
<p>    Cost and expenses			22.81 vs 7.40</p>
<p>Full name: Randgold Resources Ltd</p>
<p>Operations of Syama Gold Mine, Mali</p>
<p>			(quarter to end-Dec -- actual vs budget)</p>
<p>Gold output (ounces)			41,523 vs 35,783</p>
<p>Tonnes milled				310,000 vs 285,000</p>
<p>Cost ($/oz)					337 vs 340</p>
<p>Revenue ($/oz)				   376 vs 385</p>
<p>NOTE - Directors said Syama, acquired by Randgold Resources on October 7, 1996, was the group's first gold mine.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
